            <strong style="color: #fff;">Key Finding:</strong> At 112G PAM4 signaling (28 GHz Nyquist), a 20-layer board using standard FR-4 loses over 60% of signal energy across a 10-inch trace. With Megtron 6 + HVLP copper, that same loss drops to under 15%. This is the difference between a passing and failing eye diagram mask test.
          </p>
